# Introduction

This package creates **Dropbox Bot** for demonstrating integration between Cerb and [Dropbox's API](https://www.dropbox.com/developers/documentation/http/documentation).

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/guides/dropbox/cerb-and-dropbox.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

# Configure the Dropbox plugin

If you haven't already, follow [these instructions](/guides/integrations/dropbox/configure-plugin/) to install and configure the Dropbox plugin, and add your first connected account.

# Import the package

Navigate to **Setup >> Configure >> Import Package**.

Paste the following package into the large text box:

<pre style="max-height: 29.25em;">
<code class="language-json">
{% raw %}
{
  "package": {
    "name": "Dropbox Bot",
    "revision": 1,
    "requires": {
      "cerb_version": "8.3.0",
      "plugins": [

      ]
    },
    "configure": {
      "placeholders": [

      ],
      "prompts": [
        {
          "type": "chooser",
          "label": "Dropbox account:",
          "key": "dropbox_account_id",
          "params": {
            "context": "cerberusweb.contexts.connected_account",
            "query": "service:dropbox"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "bots": [
    {
      "uid": "bot_dropbox",
      "name": "Dropbox Bot",
      "owner": {
        "context": "cerberusweb.contexts.app",
        "id": 0
      },
      "is_disabled": false,
      "params": {
        "config": null,
        "events": {
          "mode": "all",
          "items": [

          ]
        },
        "actions": {
          "mode": "all",
          "items": [

          ]
        }
      },
      "image": "data:image/png;base64,",
      "behaviors": [
        {
          "uid": "behavior_download",
          "title": "API: POST /download",
          "is_disabled": false,
          "is_private": true,
          "priority": 50,
          "event": {
            "key": "event.macro.bot",
            "label": "Custom behavior on bot"
          },
          "nodes": [
            {
              "type": "action",
              "title": "Download via API",
              "status": "live",
              "params": {
                "actions": [
                  {
                    "action": "core.va.action.http_request",
                    "http_verb": "post",
                    "http_url": "https://content.dropboxapi.com/2/files/download",
                    "http_headers": "Content-Type: application/octet-stream\r\n{% set args = {\r\n\t\"path\": \"/cerb.png\"\r\n} %}\r\nDropbox-API-Arg: {{args|json_encode}}",
                    "http_body": "",
                    "auth": "connected_account",
                    "auth_connected_account_id": "{{{dropbox_account_id}}}",
                    "run_in_simulator": "1",
                    "response_placeholder": "_http_response"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "uid": "behavior_list_folder",
          "title": "API: POST /files/list_folder",
          "is_disabled": false,
          "is_private": true,
          "priority": 50,
          "event": {
            "key": "event.macro.bot",
            "label": "Custom behavior on bot"
          },
          "nodes": [
            {
              "type": "action",
              "title": "Execute API request",
              "status": "live",
              "params": {
                "actions": [
                  {
                    "action": "core.va.action.http_request",
                    "http_verb": "post",
                    "http_url": "https://api.dropboxapi.com/2/files/list_folder",
                    "http_headers": "Content-Type: application/json",
                    "http_body": "{# See: https://www.dropbox.com/developers/documentation/http/documentation#files-list_folder #}\r\n{% set json = {\r\n\t\"path\": \"\",\r\n\t\"recursive\": false\r\n} %}\r\n{{json|json_encode|json_pretty}}",
                    "auth": "connected_account",
                    "auth_connected_account_id": "{{{dropbox_account_id}}}",
                    "run_in_simulator": "1",
                    "response_placeholder": "_http_response"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "uid": "behavior_upload",
          "title": "API: POST /upload",
          "is_disabled": false,
          "is_private": true,
          "priority": 50,
          "event": {
            "key": "event.macro.bot",
            "label": "Custom behavior on bot"
          },
          "nodes": [
            {
              "type": "action",
              "title": "Upload via API",
              "status": "live",
              "params": {
                "actions": [
                  {
                    "action": "core.va.action.http_request",
                    "http_verb": "post",
                    "http_url": "https://content.dropboxapi.com/2/files/upload",
                    "http_headers": "Content-Type: application/octet-stream\r\n{% set args = {\r\n\t\"path\": \"/cerb.png\",\r\n\t\"mode\": \"add\",\r\n\t\"autorename\": true,\r\n\t\"mute\": false } %}\r\nDropbox-API-Arg: {{args|json_encode}}",
                    "http_body": "{# See: https://www.dropbox.com/developers/documentation/http/documentation#files-upload #}\r\n{{\"\"|base64_decode}}",
                    "auth": "connected_account",
                    "auth_connected_account_id": "{{{dropbox_account_id}}}",
                    "run_in_simulator": "1",
                    "response_placeholder": "_http_response"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]

Click the **Import** button.

You'll be prompted to link the Dropbox connected account you created earlier.

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/import.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

Click the **Import** button again.

You should see the following:

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/imported.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

# Test the example behaviors

Click on **Dropbox Bot** and then click **Behaviors** on its card.

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/bot.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/behaviors.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

## Upload a file

Open the card for the **API: POST /upload** behavior.

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/behavior-upload.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

Click on the **Simulator** button at the top of the card.

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/behavior-upload-simulate.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

Click the **Simulate** button on the popup.

You should see a JSON response with the results of your Dropbox file upload.

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/behavior-upload-simulated.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

This uploads a file named `cerb.png` to your Dropbox account.

## List files in a folder

Open the card for the **API: POST /files/list_folder** behavior.

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/behavior-list.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

Click on the **Simulator** button at the top of the card.

Click the **Simulate** button on the popup.

You should see a JSON response with the contents of your Dropbox folder.

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/behavior-list-simulated.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

## Download a file

Open the card for the **API: POST /upload** behavior.

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/behavior-download.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

Click on the **Simulator** button at the top of the card.

Click the **Simulate** button on the popup.

You should see a JSON response with the results of your Dropbox file download.

<div class="cerb-screenshot">
<img src="/assets/images/packages/dropbox-bot/behavior-download-simulated.png" class="screenshot">
</div>

The response body contains the contents of your file. The `dropbox-api-result` HTTP header contains the metadata.

# Next steps

At this point you can modify the behaviors to meet your needs.  You can use the responses from [Dropbox's API](https://www.dropbox.com/developers/documentation/http/documentation) in your behaviors.
